AGI -&nbsp;"Here in Ukraine, in our part of Europe, unfortunately we do not have the level of defense that we have seen all in the Middle East a few days ago. When, thanks to the combined force of the allies, almost all the missiles and drones that attacked Israel were shot down. We are still convinced that it is necessary to protect Europe from ballistic missiles and "Shahed", from cruise missiles and bombs, as happened in the skies of Israel and other countries of the region. Our Ukrainian sky and the sky of our neighbors deserve the same security. And I thank all those who feel our need for security also as a need for equal security for all, because all lives have the same value." The Ukrainian President, Volodymyr Zelensky, said this in his video conference at the EU summit.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;"This morning another Russian terrorist attack began in Ukraine. They hit our town in Chernihiv. Cruise missiles against civilian buildings. Many houses and a hospital were damaged, a hotel was completely destroyed. There were people under the rubble. In total, more than 60 people were injured, including children. Unfortunately 17 people were killed. And this is what happens every day. It reflects our current fundamental need: the need for air defense" added Ukrainian leader.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> European leaders collect the call
"The European Council stresses the need to provide urgent air defence to Ukraine and to speed up and intensify the supply of all necessary military assistance, including ammunition of artillery and missiles. It called on the Council, in particular at its next meeting, and the Member States to ensure the necessary follow-up. The European Council welcomes the progress made on proposals to allocate extraordinary revenue from Russia's immobilized assets to the benefit of Ukraine and calls for rapid adoption." This is what we read in the Ukraine part of the Extraordinary European Council conclusions in Brussels.
&nbsp;
"The European Council strongly condemns Russia's continued air and missile attacks against civilian population and civil and critical infrastructure in Ukraine, including the recent intensification of attacks on the energy sector. The European Union and its Member States will intensify the provision of humanitarian assistance and civil protection, including equipment such as power generators and transformers," states EU leaders in the text. Finally, the Twenty-seven points out that military support will be provided in full compliance with the security and defence policy of certain Member States and taking into account the security and defence interests of all Member States and reiterate the "full and firm" support for Ukraine.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Michel, we condemn Russia's attacks
&nbsp;"With Ukrainian President, Voloymyr Zelensky, we discussed the latest developments in Ukraine. We firmly condemn Russia's attacks on critical infrastructure, especially the energy sector. We must urgently provide air defense and accelerate the delivery of all military support, including ammunition." On X the President of the European Council, Charles Michel.&nbsp;
